َبُو ٱلۡبَشَرِ.. أُمِرَ أَنْ لَا يَأْكُلَ مِنْ تِلْكَ ٱلثَّمَرَةِ، لٰكِنَّهُ اَكَلَ، فَصَارَ بَعْدَئِذٍ بَشَرًا وَهَبَطَ إِلَىٰ ٱلۡأَرْضِ، وِإِلَّا لَكَانَ مَلَكًا لَا مِيزَةَ لَهُ، وَلَصَارَ غَيْرُهُ آدَمَ وَلَفُرِضَ عَلَيْهِ أَنْ يَسْجُدَ أَمَامَهُ، لَكِنَّهُ تَمَرَّدَ فَصَارَ آدَم.","english":"For sure the biggest human value is that from which s/he begings by \"refusing\" and \"not consenting\" that are summarised in the word \"no\" and from it began Adam the father of humanity.. He had been ordered not to eat from that fruit, but he ate, and henceforth he became a human and landed on Earth, if he had not he would have been an angel with no distinguishing feature, and someone else would have become Adam and he would have been obliged to prostrate before him, but he rebelled and so he became Adam."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to impose"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to notch, to make incisions in"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَرَضَ (faraḍa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"duty"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew פָּרַץ (pāraṣ), Aramaic פְּרַץ (pəraṣ) and Akkadian paraṣum."},"ipa":null}